      "outputs": {
        "gguf_q4_0": "Okay, here's a screenplay scene focusing on the explanation of the cheating software, aiming for a balance of tension, technical detail, and the uneasy moral implications.\n\n---\n\n**SCENE:** Leo’s Bedroom - Night\n\n**SETTING:** Leo’s room is a chaotic haven of textbooks, energy drink cans, and a glowing laptop screen. Rain streaks the window. Leo (17, anxious, bordering on frantic) paces while Finn (17, cool, collected, a coding prodigy) sits calmly at his desk, surrounded by monitors displaying lines of code.\n\n**(SOUND:** Constant, low hum of computers, rain against the window)\n\n**LEO:** (Wringing his hands) I just… I can’t do this. It’s tomorrow. The biggest exam of my life. And if I fail… Crestwood? Gone. Just… gone.\n\n**FINN:** (Without looking up) Relax. You’ve been studying. You know the material.\n\n**LEO:** Knowing the material isn’t enough! It’s *online*. Adaptive. It changes every time. Mr. Henderson practically built a Turing test for AP Bio.\n\n**FINN:** (Finally turns, a slight smirk) Okay",
        "gguf_q4_k_m": "Okay, here’s a scene draft for a screenplay, aiming for a balance of tension, humor, and a touch of moral ambiguity.\n\n---\n\n**SCENE:** Leo’s Bedroom - Night\n\n**SETTING:** Leo’s small, slightly messy bedroom. Posters of bands and video games adorn the walls. A single desk lamp illuminates a laptop open on the desk. Empty energy drink cans and crumpled notes litter the surface.\n\n**CHARACTERS:**\n\n* **LEO (17):** Anxious, stressed, bordering on frantic.\n* **SAM (17):** Cool, calm, and undeniably brilliant. He’s wearing a hoodie and has a perpetually amused expression.\n\n\n**(The scene opens with Leo pacing back and forth, running a hand through his already dishevelled hair. Sam is sitting at the desk, meticulously adjusting the settings on the laptop.)**\n\n**LEO:** (Agitated) I just… I don’t understand how I can even *think* about doing this. It feels… wrong. Really, really wrong.\n\n**SAM:** (Without looking up) Relax, Leo. It’s not like I’m asking you to rob a bank. It’s an exam. A",
        "gguf_q5_k_m": "Okay, here’s a scene draft for your screenplay, aiming for a balance of tension, technical detail, and the awkwardness of a friendship pushed to the edge.\n\n---\n\n**SCENE:** Leo’s Bedroom - Night\n\n**SETTING:** Leo’s room is a chaotic haven of textbooks, empty energy drink cans, and a perpetually messy desk. The glow of a laptop screen illuminates Leo’s anxious face. Across from him, Kai, a cool, collected coder, is meticulously adjusting settings on a separate monitor.\n\n**(SOUND:**  A low, rhythmic hum of the computer, punctuated by the click of the keyboard.)\n\n**LEO** (Voice tight with stress)\nOkay, okay, so you’re *sure* this is going to work? Like, *really* sure? Because if this blows up in my face and I get expelled, I’m blaming you.\n\n**KAI** (Without looking up, his fingers flying across the keyboard)\nRelax, Leo. It’s not some Frankenstein monster. It’s… efficient. And it’s designed to be undetectable. Mostly.\n\n**LEO**\n“Mostly”? That’s not exactly reassuring. This is Redwood University, Kai! It",
        "gguf_q8_0": "Okay, here's a screenplay scene focusing on the explanation of the cheating software, aiming for a balance of tension, technical detail, and the uneasy feeling of what’s happening.\n\n---\n\n**SCENE:** Leo’s Bedroom - Night\n\n**SETTING:** Leo’s room is a chaotic haven of textbooks, energy drink cans, and half-finished projects. The glow of a laptop screen illuminates his anxious face. Across from him, Kai, a cool, collected figure with perpetually messy hair and a focused intensity, is meticulously adjusting settings on the laptop.\n\n**CHARACTERS:**\n\n*   **LEO (17):** Stressed, desperate, bordering on panicked.\n*   **KAI (17):** Brilliant, pragmatic, a little morally ambiguous.\n\n\n**(SCENE START)**\n\n**LEO**\n(Wringing his hands)\nOkay, okay, walk me through it again. Slowly. I just... I don’t want to mess this up. This is everything.\n\n**KAI**\n(Without looking up, his fingers flying across the keyboard)\nRelax. It’s not rocket science, just… advanced automation. Think of it like a really, *really* efficient search engine."
